# cf-hono-supabase-gemini-api-template

Read **`INSTRUCTIONS.md`** first for Supabase prerequisites, env setup, and how to pair with the React frontend demo.

- Feature contract: `index.md`
- OKF skills: `.agents/skills/index.md`
- Cursor skills: `.agents/skills/README.md`
- Default API: `GET /health` (public), `GET /me` (JWT), `POST /chat` (JWT + Gemini)

When adding endpoints: register in `src/index.ts` (public before `authMiddleware`), use `successResponse`/`errorResponse`, prefer `getSupabaseClientWithJWT` for user data, update `index.md`.

Pairing frontend (not in this repo): [react-supabase-auth-ai-chat-template](https://github.com/open-templates/react-supabase-auth-ai-chat-template) — set its `VITE_API_BASE_URL` to this worker and `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` here to the frontend origin.
